00:59:44.125 --> 00:59:46.583
<i>even forced Nehru to agree...</i>

00:59:46.625 --> 00:59:51.208
<i>that there's no irrefutable proof
that Subhas Bose died in the plane crash.</i>

00:59:51.417 --> 00:59:52.458
It was so unbiased...

00:59:52.958 --> 00:59:57.542
that they ignored capable judges like Radha
Binod Pal who was there in the Tokyo trial...

00:59:58.125 --> 01:00:01.458
and appointed Khosla
who was openly anti-Subhas.

01:00:01.500 --> 01:00:05.208
Then giving him a huge post in the
Government after the verdict.

01:00:05.292 --> 01:00:07.000
It was so detailed...

01:00:07.292 --> 01:00:11.083
that the entire Commission was run
in an air conditioned room in Delhi.

01:00:11.167 --> 01:00:13.875
And another one, although
with great reluctance, in Taiwan.

01:00:14.125 --> 01:00:18.542
But more energy was spent on shopping for
the then PM rather than the investigations.

01:00:18.583 --> 01:00:21.250
You're making this political, Mr. Dhar.

01:00:21.708 --> 01:00:23.958
Which anti-Congress party
are you a member of?

01:00:24.083 --> 01:00:27.083
BJP, RSS, Bajrang Dal
or Forward Bloc?

01:00:27.417 --> 01:00:28.916
I'm not a political party cadre, Mr. Paul.

01:00:28.917 --> 01:00:30.875
I'm a soldier of the Azad Hind Fauj.

01:00:31.292 --> 01:00:32.542
I'm sure you've heard of it.

01:00:33.250 --> 01:00:35.250
Or do you want to set
up another commission?

01:00:35.333 --> 01:00:37.917
Okay, that'll be all gentlemen.

01:00:38.125 --> 01:00:39.250
Okay.

01:00:39.792 --> 01:00:41.083
Okay.

01:00:41.750 --> 01:00:46.042
The commission
will look into
the entire plane crash theory with proof...

01:00:46.208 --> 01:00:49.333
testimonials and the government
documents
you have furnished.

01:00:50.375 --> 01:00:54.083
I, personally, will travel to Taiwan,
Japan and Bangkok...

01:00:54.125 --> 01:00:56.875
to investigate
the claims
and the counter claims.

01:00:58.833 --> 01:01:01.292
But tell me something, Mr. Dhar.

01:01:02.292 --> 01:01:06.625
If Netaji Subhas Chandra Bose
did not die in the plane crash...

01:01:07.375 --> 01:01:09.167
then where did he go?

01:01:09.500 --> 01:01:11.917
I mean, according to your theory.

01:01:41.083 --> 01:01:42.917
Coming.

01:01:43.375 --> 01:01:46.042
Wait... I'm coming...

01:01:46.875 --> 01:01:47.667
Who is it?

01:01:47.668 --> 01:01:49.917
Open the door, Mishra.
The CM is here.

01:01:53.458 --> 01:01:55.333
- Good evening.
- Good evening.

01:01:55.750 --> 01:01:57.875
Hope all is well with you, Mahadeo.

01:01:57.917 --> 01:02:01.333
- Yes, My Lord.
- I'm not your lord.

01:02:01.792 --> 01:02:03.792
He's sitting inside.

01:02:03.917 --> 01:02:06.625
- Yes, that's true.
- Hello.

01:02:06.792 --> 01:02:09.708
He's expecting you.
Please come this way.

01:02:10.500 --> 01:02:14.125
- Let's go.
- This way.

01:02:16.042 --> 01:02:18.083
Watch your step.

01:02:44.542 --> 01:02:45.958
Greetings, Babaji!

01:02:46.042 --> 01:02:48.708
Welcome, Sampooran.

01:02:49.667 --> 01:02:51.625
Have you brought the books on Tantra?

01:02:51.750 --> 01:02:53.167
Yes, Babaji.

01:02:53.250 --> 01:02:54.875
Here they are.

01:02:55.333 --> 01:02:57.083
That's great.

01:02:58.375 --> 01:03:00.167
Tell me something, son.

01:03:00.917 --> 01:03:04.958
How long has our country
been independent?

01:03:05.083 --> 01:03:06.542
It's been eight years, Babaji.

01:03:07.042 --> 01:03:08.417
Eight years.

01:03:10.375 --> 01:03:12.083
Tell me.

01:03:12.833 --> 01:03:18.541
Is there a triple arch on the facade
of the UP Legislative Assembly?

01:03:18.542 --> 01:03:20.291
Yes, Babaji. Yes.

01:03:20.292 --> 01:03:24.750
There's a symbol there
from before the independence.

01:03:25.875 --> 01:03:27.333
A star.

01:03:28.083 --> 01:03:31.375
An occult-imperialist symbol.

01:03:32.333 --> 01:03:35.208
A memento of the British rule
and oppression.

01:03:35.542 --> 01:03:36.583
Really?

01:03:37.167 --> 01:03:39.208
I've never noticed.

01:03:40.042 --> 01:03:41.749
But if you're saying it might be there...

01:03:41.750 --> 01:03:45.042
I am certain it's there.

01:03:46.625 --> 01:03:49.375
But it shouldn't be there
after eight years of independence.

01:03:49.792 --> 01:03:51.000
Isn't it, Sampooran?

01:03:51.958 --> 01:03:54.625
It won't be there from tomorrow, Babaji.

01:03:54.875 --> 01:03:56.833
There's one more thing.

01:03:57.625 --> 01:03:59.875
I got a letter from Benarasi.

01:04:00.333 --> 01:04:02.458
Do you agree with him?

01:04:02.583 --> 01:04:03.833
Yes, Babaji.

01:04:04.958 --> 01:04:06.792
It's probably not my place to say it...

01:04:07.417 --> 01:04:10.542
The relationship Delhi now
has with the other countries...

01:04:10.667 --> 01:04:13.000
You should be a little careful.

01:04:13.042 --> 01:04:15.166
Therefore, on behalf of UP Government...

01:04:15.167 --> 01:04:16.958
and in my personal capacity...

01:04:17.042 --> 01:04:19.375
let me arrange for a security cover.

01:04:19.542 --> 01:04:22.125
Then you can stay here
without any worry.

01:04:23.417 --> 01:04:24.583
Thank you.

01:04:24.958 --> 01:04:27.458
Babaji, there's something else.

01:04:28.875 --> 01:04:34.958
Mishra told me
you spend the entire night coughing.

01:04:35.125 --> 01:04:38.333
Let me send you a better heater
and some more blankets.

01:04:38.750 --> 01:04:40.125
If that's okay with you.

01:04:40.375 --> 01:04:41.958
There's no need.

01:04:43.083 --> 01:04:45.000
I usually don't feel very cold.

01:04:46.333 --> 01:04:50.250
This body has experienced
the frost of Siberia.

01:04:52.167 --> 01:04:54.125
I'll take your leave now, Babaji.

01:04:55.333 --> 01:04:56.333
Okay.

01:04:57.208 --> 01:04:59.417
- Goodbye, Babaji.
- Goodbye.

01:05:49.875 --> 01:05:57.875
<i>The light of my lamp died
while I walked this lonely path</i>

01:05:59.833 --> 01:06:07.833
<i>The light of my lamp died
while I walked this lonely path</i>

01:06:09.250 --> 01:06:17.250
<i>A storm brews, oh dear!</i>

01:06:18.625 --> 01:06:23.707
<i>The storm offers me company</i>

01:06:23.708 --> 01:06:31.708
<i>The light of my lamp died
while I walked this lonely path</i>

01:06:32.750 --> 01:06:38.458
<i>While I walked this lonely path</i>

01:06:40.625 --> 01:06:43.957
<i>My Lord, a lot of people believe
in the plane crash theory...</i>

01:06:43.958 --> 01:06:48.125
Many of Netaji's family members including
his wife, the late Emily Schenkl...

01:06:48.167 --> 01:06:50.624
his brothers, Sarat and Suresh
and their children.

01:06:50.625 --> 01:06:52.166
And a lot of other people believed...

01:06:52.167 --> 01:06:54.792
that he didn't die in the plane crash.

01:06:55.583 --> 01:07:00.083
But there are a lot of theories and debates
about what happened after that.

01:07:00.458 --> 01:07:02.375
<i>Some believe he fled to Russia.</i>

01:07:02.542 --> 01:07:05.917
<i>He was taken prisoner there,
tortured and murdered.</i>

01:07:06.208 --> 01:07:07.583
My personal theory is...

01:07:08.500 --> 01:07:10.292
<i>after his staged plane crash...</i>

01:07:10.708 --> 01:07:13.667
<i>Netaji Subhas Chandra Bose
went to Russia.</i>

01:07:14.208 --> 01:07:17.958
<i>He spent some time in
Stalin's Gulag in Siberia.</i>

01:07:18.167 --> 01:07:21.667
<i>Then he went to China in 1950.
And onto Tibet.</i>

01:07:22.083 --> 01:07:26.542
<i>He started delving in yoga,
spirituality and tantra...</i>

01:07:27.292 --> 01:07:30.707
<i>Then he finally became a monk.</i>

01:07:30.708 --> 01:07:35.125
<i>He entered India through Nepal
with the help of Mahadeo Mishra.</i>

01:07:35.375 --> 01:07:36.917
<i>A monk?</i>

01:07:37.000 --> 01:07:38.042
<i>Oh yes!</i>

01:07:39.250 --> 01:07:41.250
Netaji became a monk?

01:07:42.542 --> 01:07:47.542
My Lord, what kind of nonsense is he saying
about a national hero like Netaji?

01:07:47.875 --> 01:07:49.624
What audacity!

01:07:49.625 --> 01:07:54.291
My Lord, I request the Commission
not to waste time on these stupid theories.

01:07:54.292 --> 01:07:56.583
Excuse me...
Mr. Paul... Mr. Paul...

01:07:56.708 --> 01:07:58.666
Please remember,
according to what you said...

01:07:58.667 --> 01:08:02.250
a great national hero like Netaji
is no one's personal property.

01:08:02.417 --> 01:08:04.417
If you are a relative,
not even then.

01:08:04.833 --> 01:08:07.750
The actual surname
of all free Indians is Bose.

01:08:07.792 --> 01:08:10.208
Because they're all
members of Bose's family.

01:08:10.292 --> 01:08:11.750
I'll share my theory.

01:08:11.792 --> 01:08:13.726
And I'll present my theory
with witnesses and proof in support.

01:08:13.750 --> 01:08:15.582
Please feel free to disagree.

01:08:15.583 --> 01:08:18.417
It doesn't matter to me
or my countrymen.

01:08:26.583 --> 01:08:31.416
All that is fine but...
Russia, China, a monk...

01:08:31.417 --> 01:08:35.541
My Lord, I think Chandrachur
is smoking some great weed.

01:08:35.542 --> 01:08:39.875
Otherwise, he wouldn't waste our time
with these fantasies.

01:08:40.208 --> 01:08:41.458
You're absolutely right, sir.

01:08:41.750 --> 01:08:44.250
It's the same weed Ardhendu Sarkar
used to smoke.

01:08:44.375 --> 01:08:44.958
What?

01:08:45.167 --> 01:08:46.167
Ardhendu what?

01:08:46.667 --> 01:08:47.667
Sarkar.

01:08:47.708 --> 01:08:49.417
Ardhendu Sarkar.

01:08:49.708 --> 01:08:52.917
I am a post graduate
in mechanical
engineering from UK.

01:08:53.167 --> 01:08:55.791
And I am the Chief Engineer
in the Heavy
Engineering Corporation.

01:08:55.792 --> 01:08:56.916
Yes, tell me.

01:08:56.917 --> 01:08:58.292
Right, sir.

01:08:59.208 --> 01:09:04.083
My senior at the plant, Mr. BA Zerovin
was a German Jew.

01:09:04.500 --> 01:09:07.208
And he was once in Stalin's Gulag...

01:09:08.250 --> 01:09:12.124
which is located beyond the ends
of Trans-Siberian Railways...

01:09:12.125 --> 01:09:13.791
in the vicinity of Ural mountains.

01:09:13.792 --> 01:09:15.333
Okay, go on.

01:09:21.667 --> 01:09:23.625
Sir, he told me that...

01:09:25.083 --> 01:09:31.417
he met Netaji Subhas Chandra Bose once
in the Gulag in 1948.

01:09:31.792 --> 01:09:33.417
<i>He was being treated well.</i>

01:09:34.042 --> 01:09:35.375
<i>Even given a car.</i>

01:09:36.000 --> 01:09:39.417
<i>And he was moving around
with a couple of guards there.</i>

01:09:40.250 --> 01:09:42.958
<i>But the most important thing is that...</i>

01:09:43.583 --> 01:09:47.750
Netaji Subhas Chandra Bose told Zerovin...

01:09:48.458 --> 01:09:53.750
that he would be going back to India
very soon.

01:09:57.458 --> 01:10:02.333
Mr. Sarkar,
you're a mechanical engineer, right?

01:10:02.583 --> 01:10:03.708
Yes, sir.

01:10:04.250 --> 01:10:07.166
Was Netaji also a mechanical engineer?

01:10:07.167 --> 01:10:08.750
Certainly not, sir.

01:10:09.167 --> 01:10:12.833
Then how is this information
relevant to you?

01:10:13.625 --> 01:10:15.375
No, sir... Actually...

01:10:15.667 --> 01:10:16.667
I mean...

01:10:16.708 --> 01:10:18.541
I being an Indian who...

01:10:18.542 --> 01:10:21.875
Who has come here to work
as an engineer.

01:10:22.667 --> 01:10:24.458
Not as a private eye.

01:10:24.750 --> 01:10:28.417
So if he pokes his nose
into matters of politics I'm afraid...

01:10:29.583 --> 01:10:33.167
I cannot guarantee the safety
of his nose.

01:10:33.542 --> 01:10:36.417
Or any other part of his body
for that matter.

01:10:36.917 --> 01:10:38.375
Is that clear?

01:10:39.083 --> 01:10:40.292
Yes, sir.

01:10:40.750 --> 01:10:41.750
Yes.

01:10:42.250 --> 01:10:43.457
Just one other thing...

01:10:43.458 --> 01:10:45.999
Could you please repeat
what you just told me?

01:10:46.000 --> 01:10:46.708
Of course.

01:10:47.000 --> 01:10:48.792
My senior Mr. Zerovin had...

01:10:55.542 --> 01:10:57.042
I mean I...

01:10:58.958 --> 01:11:00.917
I really don't remember...

01:11:01.917 --> 01:11:04.417
whatever I have told you right now.

01:11:05.703 --> 01:11:06.703
Excellent!

01:11:07.167 --> 01:11:08.917
Remember that you don't remember.

01:11:09.300 --> 01:11:10.300
You may leave now.

01:11:11.445 --> 01:11:14.820
That day he returned home terrified.

01:11:15.250 --> 01:11:18.958
After that, he didn't say anything
to anyone for years out of fear.

01:11:19.070 --> 01:11:21.070
Until, I interviewed him
last year.

01:11:21.721 --> 01:11:22.721
Okay.

01:11:23.125 --> 01:11:26.750
This Commission will record his testimony.

01:11:27.167 --> 01:11:30.292
Do you think we should call
any other witnesses?

01:11:30.458 --> 01:11:31.833
Yes, My Lord.
I think so.

01:11:32.625 --> 01:11:37.124
Famous Tibetologist, Rahul Ram
could have provided a strong testimony.

01:11:37.125 --> 01:11:40.207
Whereby, my theory
would've been proved beyond doubt.

01:11:40.208 --> 01:11:41.208
But...

01:11:41.625 --> 01:11:42.917
We're late.

01:11:43.000 --> 01:11:47.207
In fact, the pre-RAW, Ministry of External
Affairs' Govt. Intelligence Officer...

01:11:47.208 --> 01:11:50.542
he was late too.

01:11:51.125 --> 01:11:55.583
Yadav, I have a secret.

01:11:56.125 --> 01:12:00.958
I won't be able to die in peace with it.

01:12:01.042 --> 01:12:02.417
Nothing will happen to you.

01:12:02.500 --> 01:12:03.375
Keep quiet.

01:12:03.417 --> 01:12:04.333
The doctor's on his way.

01:12:04.334 --> 01:12:06.042
- Don't talk.
- Please let me speak.

01:12:07.292 --> 01:12:10.875
I don't have much time.

01:12:11.125 --> 01:12:13.292
Okay, tell me.
Go ahead.

01:12:13.708 --> 01:12:18.958
Do you remember Babajaan Gouffral?

01:12:19.208 --> 01:12:22.167
Gouffral... That Soviet official?

01:12:22.208 --> 01:12:24.291
He was a good friend of Stalin.

01:12:24.292 --> 01:12:25.833
He was quite close to you too.

01:12:26.083 --> 01:12:27.083
Yeah.

01:12:27.333 --> 01:12:28.333
Yes.

01:12:28.458 --> 01:12:30.167
He once told me...

01:12:30.625 --> 01:12:36.083
Netaji Subhas Chandra Bose in 1945...

01:12:37.042 --> 01:12:41.750
had entered Russia through Manchuria.

01:12:42.083 --> 01:12:43.083
What?

01:12:43.667 --> 01:12:46.250
- But the plane crash...
- Was a lie!

01:12:46.417 --> 01:12:49.792
I'm not making this up.

01:12:52.292 --> 01:12:54.000
This is the truth.

01:12:54.125 --> 01:12:56.750
And you...

01:12:57.000 --> 01:13:00.625
You will share this information
with everyone...

01:13:01.042 --> 01:13:09.042
when this country is ready
to hear the truth about Netaji.

01:13:10.375 --> 01:13:12.875
And this was his dying declaration.

01:13:12.917 --> 01:13:14.249
So, Mr. Paul...

01:13:14.250 --> 01:13:18.042
there were other famous people
smoking the same weed.

01:13:18.250 --> 01:13:19.957
Anyway, let me get back to main issue.

01:13:19.958 --> 01:13:22.332
Let me tell you
about the mysterious old man.

01:13:22.333 --> 01:13:26.000
He had a lot of different names.

01:13:26.083 --> 01:13:30.875
Like Pardewale Baba,
Anaam Sant,
Bhagwanji or...

01:13:32.208 --> 01:13:34.000
Gumnaami Baba.

01:13:35.167 --> 01:13:38.582
<i>When Netaji settled in Lucknow in 1955...</i>

01:13:38.583 --> 01:13:41.457
<i>to live the rest of his life in secret...</i>

01:13:41.458 --> 01:13:42.999
<i>he didn't know it then...</i>

01:13:43.000 --> 01:13:45.708
<i>that a moment of carelessness...</i>

01:13:45.958 --> 01:13:47.749
<i>could expose his secret.</i>

01:13:47.750 --> 01:13:52.125
<i>And that he would have to keep moving
all over Uttar Pradesh frequently.</i>

01:13:52.167 --> 01:13:56.833
<i>Because people got to know his
real identity in just a few days.</i>

01:13:58.292 --> 01:14:02.125
- Please come in, Guruji. This way.
- Greetings!

01:14:06.667 --> 01:14:08.750
Please come in.

01:14:13.875 --> 01:14:16.708
I've heard Mr. Gandhi used to
get his glasses from here.

01:14:17.250 --> 01:14:18.500
Yes, Guruji.

01:14:19.167 --> 01:14:22.125
But how does that...
I mean...

01:14:22.458 --> 01:14:23.375
You don't have a...

01:14:23.417 --> 01:14:27.791
Maybe, our visions are different.
Even the far-sighted ones.

01:14:27.792 --> 01:14:32.458
But that doesn't mean
we can't buy glasses from the same shop.

01:14:35.125 --> 01:14:38.750
Guruji, please check if
you can read clearly.

01:14:38.792 --> 01:14:40.458
This is correct.

01:14:40.917 --> 01:14:42.458
- Is this okay?
- Yes.

01:14:43.083 --> 01:14:47.792
We're done here.
Let's select a frame now.

01:14:48.375 --> 01:14:49.375
Let's go.

01:15:34.000 --> 01:15:39.333
Oh my God! Netaji!
Netaji is sitting here.

01:15:39.625 --> 01:15:40.708
Come and see.

01:15:41.250 --> 01:15:42.958
How did you come here?

01:15:43.000 --> 01:15:45.083
That's not Netaji.
Please move.

01:15:49.333 --> 01:15:50.333
<i>Brilliant!</i>

01:15:51.000 --> 01:15:53.500
You should have been a screenplay writer!

01:15:53.792 --> 01:15:55.792
Anyway, tell me, Mr. Dhar.

01:15:56.125 --> 01:16:01.375
How did an activist, a
fiercely political man...

01:16:01.708 --> 01:16:07.125
suddenly became a god-fearing,
shy monk in hiding?

01:16:07.208 --> 01:16:08.208
How?

01:16:08.625 --> 01:16:09.917
Suddenly, sir.

01:16:10.250 --> 01:16:16.082
Just like a brown Sahib who made racist
comments against the African natives...

01:16:16.083 --> 01:16:19.375
suddenly became a cotton loincloth
wearing 'Mahatma'.

01:16:19.625 --> 01:16:21.542
Just like a bomb making daredevil...

01:16:21.583 --> 01:16:23.000
but a violent revolutionary...

01:16:23.042 --> 01:16:26.333
suddenly became a peace loving
and spiritual guru.

01:16:26.958 --> 01:16:29.708
That's life, sir. Life.

01:16:30.125 --> 01:16:33.167
Life and it's different ways.

01:16:33.208 --> 01:16:35.875
It can change you forever.

01:16:36.167 --> 01:16:40.124
Though unlike Mohandas Karamchand Gandhi
or Aurobindo Ghosh...

01:16:40.125 --> 01:16:44.917
Netaji's transformation was not sudden
or unexpected.

01:16:45.250 --> 01:16:48.042
He had a history of spirituality.

01:16:48.708 --> 01:16:53.042
In his youth, he had run away from home
several times in search of a teacher.

01:16:53.625 --> 01:16:57.750
He knew the the ancient religious texts
by heart.

01:16:58.208 --> 01:17:01.292
He prayed to Goddesses Durga,
Kali and Shakti.

01:17:01.833 --> 01:17:03.875
He regularly practised yoga.

01:17:03.958 --> 01:17:05.375
I get that.

01:17:05.458 --> 01:17:09.957
But do you have any admissable evidence
apart from your stories?

01:17:09.958 --> 01:17:14.792
Someone who knew him...
Old friends, relatives, companions...

01:17:15.042 --> 01:17:17.332
People who knew that Gumnaami Baba
as Netaji.

01:17:17.333 --> 01:17:22.000
Do you think I'll waste your time
if I didn't have the evidence?

01:17:22.292 --> 01:17:25.875
There are many relatives
and friends like that.

01:17:26.125 --> 01:17:28.167
People who had recognised him as Netaji.

01:17:28.625 --> 01:17:31.792
And there are signs of this recognition
in letters written to Gumnaami Baba...

01:17:31.917 --> 01:17:36.333
that prove beyond doubt and which I have
already submitted to the Commission.

01:17:36.708 --> 01:17:37.832
But among them...

01:17:37.833 --> 01:17:40.207
I want to mention two people specially...

01:17:40.208 --> 01:17:43.333
who after they recognised him...

01:17:43.708 --> 01:17:46.083
reacted in two different ways.

01:17:46.333 --> 01:17:47.333
<i>Greetings!</i>

01:17:47.458 --> 01:17:49.291
My name is Atul Sen.

01:17:49.292 --> 01:17:50.958
<i>I have come from Calcutta.</i>

01:17:51.417 --> 01:17:54.042
<i>I want to meet Pardewala Baba once.</i>

01:17:54.417 --> 01:17:56.249
<i>He doesn't meet anyone.</i>

01:17:56.250 --> 01:17:59.082
<i>Even if he speaks to someone,
he stays behind a curtain.</i>

01:17:59.083 --> 01:18:01.207
<i>I've come a long way.</i>

01:18:01.208 --> 01:18:03.082
<i>I've heard a lot about him.</i>

01:18:03.083 --> 01:18:07.125
<i>Even if I got a chance to hear him,
I would be at peace.</i>

01:18:07.583 --> 01:18:11.417
How are you, Atul?
How is your family?

01:18:12.000 --> 01:18:14.625
You... You...

01:18:15.417 --> 01:18:17.917
I mean... I bow to you, Guruji.

01:18:18.000 --> 01:18:23.708
You've always spoken Hindi with a
Bengali accent, just like me, Atul.

01:18:23.781 --> 01:18:27.656
So, say whatever you want
in Bengali.

01:18:28.000 --> 01:18:29.750
You, I mean... You...

01:18:29.792 --> 01:18:31.208
Are you surprised?

01:18:31.333 --> 01:18:32.833
Are you really him?

01:18:32.875 --> 01:18:37.875
The one who helped me
win the Dhaka Municipal elections?

01:18:39.793 --> 01:18:40.793
No.

01:18:41.583 --> 01:18:43.000
He has died.

01:18:45.417 --> 01:18:47.000
That man is dead.

01:18:47.083 --> 01:18:49.457
<i>Mine is not mere belief
but actual knowledge...</i>

01:18:49.458 --> 01:18:52.957
<i>that Netaji is alive
and is engaged in spiritual practice...</i>

01:18:52.958 --> 01:18:54.041
<i>somewhere in India.</i>

01:18:54.042 --> 01:18:56.582
<i>I deliberately make the
location a little vague...</i>

01:18:56.583 --> 01:19:00.333
<i>because of the talks I had with him
for months together not very long ago.</i>

01:19:00.375 --> 01:19:05.041
<i>I could understand that he is yet regarded
as enemy number one of the Allied powers.</i>

01:19:05.042 --> 01:19:06.541
<i>And there's a secret protocol...</i>

01:19:06.542 --> 01:19:11.208
<i>that binds the
Government of India
to deliver him
to Allied justice if found alive.</i>

01:19:11.250 --> 01:19:18.124
<i>Despite being asked to keep it a secret,
Atul Sen wrote to Pundit Nehru.</i>

01:19:18.125 --> 01:19:20.166
<i>And surprisingly, Pundit Nehru...</i>

01:19:20.167 --> 01:19:24.874
<i>despite his supported theory
of Netaji dying in a plane crash...</i>

01:19:24.875 --> 01:19:27.707
<i>took the letter very seriously.</i>

01:19:27.708 --> 01:19:29.958
<i>And he personally replied to the letter.</i>

01:19:30.208 --> 01:19:32.708
<i>Because of Prof. Atul
Sen's over excitement...</i>

01:19:32.792 --> 01:19:35.250
<i>he never got to see Gumnaami Baba again...</i>

01:19:35.417 --> 01:19:39.208
<i>Dr. Pabitra Mohan Roy's case
was on the other side of the spectrum.</i>

01:19:39.500 --> 01:19:41.458
<i>A trusted comrade of Netaji.</i>

01:19:41.500 --> 01:19:44.750
<i>One of the four members
of the INA's secret service.</i>

01:19:45.083 --> 01:19:49.667
<i>Who had travelled to Kolkata in a submarine
to handle the guerilla units of INA.</i>

01:19:49.833 --> 01:19:53.208
<i>He immediately recognised Netaji
in the Gumnaami Baba outfit.</i>

01:19:53.833 --> 01:19:55.249
<i>But this information...</i>

01:19:55.250 --> 01:19:59.208
<i>he kept it a secret
till the last day of his life.</i>

01:19:59.250 --> 01:20:01.041
<i>After Gumnaami Baba's death...</i>

01:20:01.042 --> 01:20:05.249
<i>when the Police and CBI
found hundreds of letters written to him...</i>

01:20:05.250 --> 01:20:09.583
<i>where it became clear that he was
addressing Gumnaami Baba as Netaji.</i>

01:20:09.833 --> 01:20:12.583
<i>He faced gruelling interrogation.</i>

01:20:12.792 --> 01:20:16.625
There are similarities between Gumnaami
Baba and Netaji's handwriting.

01:20:16.875 --> 01:20:22.917
Can you please tell me clearly
whether he was or wasn't Netaji?

01:20:23.667 --> 01:20:27.333
I could never understand
if he was Netaji or not.

01:20:31.917 --> 01:20:33.750
You have some letters from him.

01:20:33.833 --> 01:20:35.208
Show it to us.

01:20:36.292 --> 01:20:38.458
I had received a few letters.

01:20:38.958 --> 01:20:41.250
But I didn't keep them.
I've thrown them away.

01:20:41.917 --> 01:20:44.708
But then who was he?

01:20:46.625 --> 01:20:48.000
I don't know.

01:20:49.000 --> 01:20:53.458
We've a lot of things belonging to Netaji
in Gumnaami Baba's room.

01:20:55.013 --> 01:20:57.138
What's your opinion on the matter?

01:20:58.542 --> 01:21:01.249
Some say he's alive.
Others say he isn't.

01:21:01.250 --> 01:21:03.375
What do you have to say?

01:21:03.833 --> 01:21:06.583
What does it matter what I say?

01:21:07.625 --> 01:21:12.083
Didn't you ever feel that Gumnaami Baba
could be Netaji?

01:21:14.042 --> 01:21:17.499
I've never met him face to face.

01:21:17.500 --> 01:21:22.833
But you've heard both their voices.

01:21:23.875 --> 01:21:25.917
Did they sound alike?

01:21:31.292 --> 01:21:32.750
Was Gumnaami Baba a Bengali?

01:21:35.125 --> 01:21:36.125
Yes.

01:21:36.833 --> 01:21:41.250
Dr. Roy, can you deny
that he was Netaji?

01:21:41.625 --> 01:21:43.167
What do you want me to deny?

01:21:43.417 --> 01:21:45.708
I've already told you
what I had to say.

01:21:46.917 --> 01:21:51.667
But what will we tell the police
and people of Faizabad?

01:21:52.042 --> 01:21:54.292
Tell them what I told you.

01:21:55.500 --> 01:21:59.750
But they're all saying that he's Netaji.

01:22:01.208 --> 01:22:04.458
Then let what's happening, happen.

01:22:05.375 --> 01:22:10.625
But Pabitra Mohan Roy
ultimately didn't say anything.

01:22:11.333 --> 01:22:15.292
He kept the whole thing
shrouded in doubt.

01:22:16.667 --> 01:22:19.833
Thank you.
Thank you, Mr. Dhar.

01:22:20.667 --> 01:22:23.625
We'll notify your next date of testifying.

01:22:23.958 --> 01:22:26.417
The Commission is adjourned for the day.

01:22:29.917 --> 01:22:32.207
- What are you doing here?
- Get in.

01:22:32.208 --> 01:22:33.582
- What's the matter?
- Get in the car. We need to talk.

01:22:33.583 --> 01:22:35.500
- What?
- Come on.

01:22:38.875 --> 01:22:39.875
What is it?

01:22:40.792 --> 01:22:43.458
Get rid of the cigarette.
I want to switch on the AC.

01:22:49.167 --> 01:22:50.666
What are you researching on now?

01:22:50.667 --> 01:22:52.375
What else?
Netaji. Gumnaami Baba.

01:22:52.500 --> 01:22:54.458
I've formed a group called Mission Netaji.
Why?

01:22:54.542 --> 01:22:56.249
I mean is it dangerous?

01:22:56.250 --> 01:22:57.667
What has happened?

01:22:58.667 --> 01:23:01.417
I got a call last night.
He was speaking in Hindi.

01:23:02.083 --> 01:23:03.833
Asked me to warn my ex-husband.

01:23:04.083 --> 01:23:06.542
To not play with fire.
Not delve into Netaji...

01:23:06.875 --> 01:23:08.167
To go back being a journo.

01:23:08.250 --> 01:23:08.958
What did you say?

01:23:08.959 --> 01:23:11.917
I said if I don't help, you'll
kill him right? Please kill him.

01:23:12.000 --> 01:23:13.417
I'll help in whatever way I can.

01:23:13.667 --> 01:23:15.375
The a... e doesn't deserve to live.

01:23:15.708 --> 01:23:16.750
He just hung up.

01:23:21.625 --> 01:23:23.250
Are you trying to help?

01:23:23.833 --> 01:23:25.667
Do you have a sniper back there?

01:23:26.167 --> 01:23:28.125
Stop kidding.

01:23:28.250 --> 01:23:30.083
You've done whatever you want
all your life.

01:23:30.375 --> 01:23:31.496
You've never listened to me.

01:23:32.125 --> 01:23:33.625
Please listen to me.

01:23:34.250 --> 01:23:35.417
Do something else.

01:23:35.750 --> 01:23:37.458
Too late for that, Roni.

01:23:37.833 --> 01:23:40.000
The problem are these glasses.

01:23:40.333 --> 01:23:42.250
I see everything through them.

01:23:42.750 --> 01:23:44.958
Okay. Do whatever you want.

01:23:45.375 --> 01:23:47.875
How have you been?
Do you miss me?

01:23:47.958 --> 01:23:49.458
Why should I?

01:23:49.833 --> 01:23:50.833
No way.

01:23:53.792 --> 01:23:55.917
You're just incorrigible.

01:23:57.208 --> 01:23:58.583
Flirting with your ex-wife?

01:23:58.750 --> 01:24:01.833
Today the testimony
which this
Commission will examine...

01:24:01.958 --> 01:24:05.750
in the matter of the identity
of Gumnaami Baba...

01:24:06.042 --> 01:24:07.292
is that of...

01:24:09.208 --> 01:24:13.208
Mr. Shrikant Sharma Kanha.

01:24:15.083 --> 01:24:16.542
Greetings!

01:24:16.875 --> 01:24:22.208
So, Mr. Sharma, please tell the Commission
what you know about Gumnaami Baba.

01:24:22.458 --> 01:24:26.000
I live in Sitapur.

01:24:27.667 --> 01:24:34.958
I had met Netaji for the first time
in 1938.

01:24:35.167 --> 01:24:37.917
I had even spoken to him.

01:24:38.542 --> 01:24:46.542
He was on a tour of UP at that time
as the Congress President.

01:24:50.708 --> 01:24:58.708
After that I met him at Neemsar
in 1963.

01:25:01.125 --> 01:25:06.083
He was living there as a monk.

01:25:06.417 --> 01:25:12.458
Some people called him Gumnaami Baba.

01:25:12.958 --> 01:25:15.708
Some people called him Bhagwanji.

01:25:16.250 --> 01:25:19.625
And some people called him
Bhik Manga Bachha.

01:25:21.083 --> 01:25:25.458
- I've heard a lot about you...
- Are you a poet?

01:25:27.875 --> 01:25:31.083
Shrikant Sharma Kanha...

01:25:33.042 --> 01:25:36.625
I've heard you're a poet.

01:25:38.000 --> 01:25:39.250
Is it true?

01:25:39.375 --> 01:25:42.208
Yes... Yes...

01:25:43.125 --> 01:25:44.875
Yes, Bhagwanji.

01:25:46.458 --> 01:25:52.625
Bhagwanji, your voice sounds very familiar.

01:25:53.917 --> 01:25:59.042
Did you come to Sitapur in 1938?

01:26:00.417 --> 01:26:04.708
Do you know why you can meet me?

01:26:07.125 --> 01:26:08.625
No, Bhagwanji.

01:26:08.917 --> 01:26:13.333
Because where sunlight can't reach...

01:26:14.042 --> 01:26:17.500
A poet's verses can.

01:26:19.750 --> 01:26:21.083
Thank you.

01:26:21.708 --> 01:26:24.042
- But...
- That's all for today.

01:26:25.333 --> 01:26:27.083
Come back tomorrow.

01:26:27.750 --> 01:26:31.625
I didn't get to see him that day.

01:26:32.500 --> 01:26:39.042
But after a few days I had become
his close confidant.

01:26:40.625 --> 01:26:44.875
He had even called me inside his room.

01:26:49.708 --> 01:26:55.625
When I saw him...
When I heard him speak...

01:26:56.000 --> 01:27:00.125
I had no doubt...

01:27:00.542 --> 01:27:05.750
that he was our Netaji Subhas Chandra Bose.

01:27:05.958 --> 01:27:10.083
Bhagwanji, the country
you won freedom for...

01:27:10.500 --> 01:27:12.917
The people you showed the light to...

01:27:13.875 --> 01:27:15.792
Why don't you appear in front of them?

01:27:18.708 --> 01:27:23.500
What you call independence, Kanha...

01:27:25.125 --> 01:27:27.125
was just an agreement...

01:27:28.917 --> 01:27:35.333
between a few leaders
and the British Empire.

01:27:37.000 --> 01:27:44.458
A disgusting agreement,
the price of which was the Partition.

01:27:47.042 --> 01:27:55.042
I have renounced politics
and the world, anyway.

01:27:56.292 --> 01:28:04.292
And if I, a war criminal
for the Allied powers reveal myself now...

01:28:04.792 --> 01:28:09.625
my country heavily dependent
on Allied powers...

01:28:11.708 --> 01:28:14.208
will suffer a lot of losses.

01:28:17.167 --> 01:28:19.458
There's going to be loss, anyway.

01:28:20.458 --> 01:28:23.958
- China has attacked...
- This was not an attack.

01:28:24.542 --> 01:28:27.500
This was just a gentle kick in the back.

01:28:28.500 --> 01:28:30.792
It's good for the country.

01:28:31.625 --> 01:28:39.625
At least, the JLN combine will now know
that non-violence can't defend the borders.

01:28:40.417 --> 01:28:45.166
They can write as many patriotic film songs
as they want...

01:28:45.167 --> 01:28:49.250
but we needed weapons
to win this freedom.

01:28:49.583 --> 01:28:53.125
JLN combine... As in?

01:28:54.167 --> 01:28:57.833
My special friend in Delhi.

01:28:59.167 --> 01:29:00.667
I get it.

01:29:02.625 --> 01:29:05.042
Can I ask you something?

01:29:07.583 --> 01:29:08.917
Go ahead, son.

01:29:11.833 --> 01:29:14.708
Was there really an accident that day?

01:29:17.917 --> 01:29:20.875
No plane took off that day.

01:29:22.708 --> 01:29:30.625
Much before the crash, your dead man
had already reached his destination.

01:29:34.292 --> 01:29:35.833
Then one day...

01:29:36.708 --> 01:29:44.708
his long time friend and freedom fighter,
Leela Roy...

01:29:45.917 --> 01:29:51.542
came to Neemsar after she heard of him.

01:29:52.708 --> 01:29:57.750
She tried very hard to meet him.

01:29:58.083 --> 01:30:01.375
She sent a lot of things too.

01:30:02.792 --> 01:30:07.958
But Bhagwanji didn't meet her.

01:30:09.708 --> 01:30:16.167
And one day she sent a message
through me.

01:30:16.208 --> 01:30:18.625
<i>I've been here since the 23rd.</i>

01:30:18.833 --> 01:30:21.875
<i>But I've been unable to establish
any contact with you.</i>

01:30:22.000 --> 01:30:25.750
<i>If you need to see proof of identity...</i>

01:30:25.917 --> 01:30:28.167
<i>I can arrange for that too.</i>

01:30:28.292 --> 01:30:31.333
<i>I had expected that I will receive orders
to establish contact.</i>

01:30:31.500 --> 01:30:35.667
<i>But I don't know why it hasn't come.</i>

01:30:36.583 --> 01:30:38.250
What did Gandhi say?

01:30:38.708 --> 01:30:40.583
Non-violence is our religion.

01:30:40.833 --> 01:30:42.833
And that's why I'm a violent terrorist.

01:30:42.875 --> 01:30:48.374
Great! That means Kshudiram Bose, Prafulla
Chaki, Binoy, Badal, Dinesh, Bhagat Singh...

01:30:48.375 --> 01:30:49.958
All are violent terrorists!

01:30:50.375 --> 01:30:52.042
And our armed revolution?

01:30:52.292 --> 01:30:57.625
Deepali Sangha, Sree Sangha, Chottograam
armoury raid were all for nothing?

01:30:57.792 --> 01:31:00.541
I've decided to resign Leela, Anil.

01:31:00.542 --> 01:31:02.875
I'll create a new party
called Forward Bloc.

01:31:03.083 --> 01:31:04.625
What a relief, Subhas!

01:31:05.000 --> 01:31:08.624
I had asked you
not to make me join Congress.

01:31:08.625 --> 01:31:11.208
I don't belong here.

01:31:11.583 --> 01:31:14.224
You took me from Sree Sangha
and sent me to the Planning Committee.

01:31:15.750 --> 01:31:18.375
- Bhagwanji?
- Yes.

01:31:20.708 --> 01:31:29.636
Tell Leela Devi and Prof. Samar Guha
that I have received their gift.

01:31:31.833 --> 01:31:40.385
Tell her I loved the sweets
that she made.

01:31:41.542 --> 01:31:46.042
I can't meet them.

01:31:46.792 --> 01:31:51.542
But if they want to talk to me then...

01:31:56.667 --> 01:31:58.417
How are you, Lee?

01:32:00.333 --> 01:32:01.500
How are you, Samar?

01:32:01.542 --> 01:32:04.583
Su... Subhas?

01:32:04.708 --> 01:32:09.958
No one called Subhas lives here, Leela.

01:32:11.292 --> 01:32:17.208
The one you're talking about
is a completely different person.

01:32:18.083 --> 01:32:20.417
I'm a monk with many names.

01:32:20.708 --> 01:32:28.458
After one becomes a monk, the earlier
life becomes like an earlier birth.

01:32:29.750 --> 01:32:36.417
There's a lot of difference
between that dead man and this body.

01:32:37.000 --> 01:32:40.208
You're very angry, Subhas.
Aren't you?

01:32:43.333 --> 01:32:44.708
Anger?

01:32:45.667 --> 01:32:49.875
Someone who is an orphan
even though his parents are alive...

01:32:50.500 --> 01:32:55.583
Someone who is alone
even though he has siblings...

01:32:56.208 --> 01:33:01.875
Someone who is an refugee
in his own country...

01:33:01.917 --> 01:33:05.917
So much so that he can't even
call his country his own...

01:33:06.667 --> 01:33:11.083
How can he be angry?

01:33:11.625 --> 01:33:15.042
Yes, he might feel hurt.

01:33:18.875 --> 01:33:22.750
You may leave now.
Take care.

01:33:24.042 --> 01:33:26.917
Please write to me often.

01:33:46.917 --> 01:33:50.833
JOYSHREE
FOUNDING EDITOR LEELA ROY

01:33:53.792 --> 01:33:56.000
Thank you, My Lord.

01:33:56.292 --> 01:33:58.500
My name is Sunil Gupta.

01:33:59.000 --> 01:34:00.625
I'm a lawyer by profession.

01:34:01.625 --> 01:34:07.917
My family members have been involved
with India's freedom struggle.

01:34:08.500 --> 01:34:15.333
Dinesh Gupta, from the
Binoy-Badal-Dinesh trio is my brother.

01:34:15.875 --> 01:34:22.082
When Suresh Bose,
Subhas Chandra Bose's brother...

01:34:22.083 --> 01:34:27.167
heard the rumours that Gumnaami Baba
was Netaji...

01:34:27.375 --> 01:34:30.000
he had sent me
to find out the truth.

01:34:30.083 --> 01:34:34.208
Because I knew Netaji very well.

01:34:35.125 --> 01:34:38.167
When I came back with the news...

01:34:39.208 --> 01:34:42.374
Suresh, I'm certain.

01:34:42.375 --> 01:34:45.374
I'll not make a mistake
in recognising Subhas.

01:34:45.375 --> 01:34:51.792
That voice, politics, religion,
literature, science...

01:34:52.083 --> 01:34:54.417
in-depth knowledge
about different subjects...

01:34:55.708 --> 01:34:59.708
The country, the social system...

01:34:59.833 --> 01:35:04.750
- His anger about the Partition.
- Are you sure?

01:35:06.417 --> 01:35:08.833
He is Subhas?

01:35:13.875 --> 01:35:16.333
He won't come back home?

01:35:18.000 --> 01:35:24.125
No, Suresh.
He said it'll be harmful for everyone.

01:35:24.917 --> 01:35:27.500
Many people will be in danger.

01:35:29.750 --> 01:35:32.457
He has renounced worldly desires.

01:35:32.458 --> 01:35:35.750
Looked like his pride was hurt.

01:35:35.875 --> 01:35:40.208
Actually, the way India was
supposed to respond at that time...

01:35:40.500 --> 01:35:41.917
That didn't happen.

01:35:41.958 --> 01:35:47.000
Yes, we all have let him down.

01:35:48.417 --> 01:35:53.167
Okay... Let him live his own way.

01:35:54.125 --> 01:35:56.458
I'll write to him.

01:35:56.833 --> 01:35:58.625
Please take the letter to him.

01:35:59.000 --> 01:36:02.958
Please arrange for whatever he needs.

01:36:03.333 --> 01:36:11.333
Money, books, magazines,
newspapers, records, anything he needs.

01:36:16.625 --> 01:36:24.625
And on his birthday, take some sweets
and Hilsa fish.

01:36:30.583 --> 01:36:33.583
He really loved it...

01:36:34.542 --> 01:36:35.583
Loves it...

01:36:36.833 --> 01:36:42.707
<i>Fields of golden grains,
meadows of fragrant flowers</i>

01:36:42.708 --> 01:36:48.708
<i>This world of ours</i>

01:36:48.792 --> 01:36:54.457
<i>Nestled amongst it is a country</i>

01:36:54.458 --> 01:36:58.749
<i>The greatest country in the world</i>

01:36:58.750 --> 01:37:06.750
<i>Created from dreams,
anchored by memories</i>

01:37:09.917 --> 01:37:17.917
<i>Nowhere else will you find
such a glorious country</i>

01:37:21.625 --> 01:37:27.707
<i>She is the queen of all countries</i>

01:37:27.708 --> 01:37:35.708
<i>That's my Motherland</i>

01:37:50.708 --> 01:37:55.667
Bhagwanji, why don't you quit smoking?

01:37:56.583 --> 01:37:59.375
What if you fall ill at this age?

01:38:06.917 --> 01:38:10.167
Have you heard of Winston Churchill, Panda?

01:38:10.250 --> 01:38:13.750
No, Bhagwanji.
Who was he?

01:38:15.583 --> 01:38:20.708
He was an as... e of the first order.

01:38:21.375 --> 01:38:26.167
He took away all our country's crops
and caused drought...

01:38:26.208 --> 01:38:30.667
that killed 30 lakh Bengalis.

01:38:31.667 --> 01:38:37.167
He was as oppressive as Hitler.

01:38:38.958 --> 01:38:44.792
When I escaped in 1941...

01:38:45.542 --> 01:38:51.875
he issued a shoot-at-sight order for me.

01:38:53.750 --> 01:38:58.750
But they couldn't catch me.

01:38:59.917 --> 01:39:03.042
Did he die of smoking too?

01:39:04.167 --> 01:39:06.000
That's the thing.

01:39:06.667 --> 01:39:10.292
That as... he lived a very long life.

01:39:11.125 --> 01:39:14.458
That too he smoked cigars not cigarettes.

01:39:16.125 --> 01:39:19.333
What health are you talking about, Panda?

01:39:22.000 --> 01:39:23.000
Bhagwanji.

01:39:24.458 --> 01:39:30.083
Bhagwanji? Bhagwanji? Bhagwanji?

01:39:30.208 --> 01:39:31.208
Saraswati!

01:39:31.250 --> 01:39:33.875
- Banerjee, we need a cylinder!
- I'll get it.

01:39:42.000 --> 01:39:46.125
I've asked for a cylinder.
Banerjee is getting it.

01:39:46.167 --> 01:39:51.458
Turn off the lights, Panda.

01:39:54.958 --> 01:40:00.583
I want to sleep now.

01:40:07.708 --> 01:40:14.333
The person whose funeral should have
been attended by 13 lakh people...

01:40:14.833 --> 01:40:18.083
there are just 13 of us here.

01:40:18.458 --> 01:40:21.000
My India is great!

01:40:21.750 --> 01:40:27.416
<i>The immense love
of my mother and brothers</i>

01:40:27.417 --> 01:40:33.458
<i>Where else will one find such pure love?</i>

01:40:33.625 --> 01:40:41.625
<i>Let me touch your feet, oh Mother,
in deep adoration</i>

01:40:44.333 --> 01:40:52.333
<i>This is the country of my birth
And I hope to breathe my last here</i>

01:40:57.208 --> 01:41:05.208
<i>Nowhere else will you find
such a glorious country</i>

01:41:09.167 --> 01:41:15.332
<i>She is the queen of all the countries</i>

01:41:15.333 --> 01:41:23.333
<i>That's my Motherland</i>

01:41:36.167 --> 01:41:38.708
<i>Guptar Ghat near Sarayu river...</i>

01:41:39.083 --> 01:41:43.333
<i>where Lord Rama also ended his life
by stepping into the river.</i>

01:41:43.542 --> 01:41:47.375
<i>His life ended in a military cantonment
close by.</i>

01:41:48.458 --> 01:41:54.124
<i>Obviously, questions were raised because an ordinary
monk's last rites took place in a military base.</i>

01:41:54.125 --> 01:41:56.582
<i>An ordinary monk?
What are you saying?</i>

01:41:56.583 --> 01:42:01.042
<i>He used to advise the army on big wars
like Vietnam war, Bangladesh war.</i>

01:42:01.083 --> 01:42:02.749
<i>He must have been a great man.</i>

01:42:02.750 --> 01:42:04.542
<i>Liar! Cheat! Fraud!</i>

01:42:04.625 --> 01:42:06.333
<i>See, Mr. Paul...</i>

01:42:06.458 --> 01:42:13.582
<i>Although most civilians wouldn't have access
to military information like he did...</i>

01:42:13.583 --> 01:42:17.749
<i>But I believe, he claimed a lot of things
that were inconsistent...</i>

01:42:17.750 --> 01:42:23.999
<i>unbelievable, exaggerated,
delusional and halucinatory too.</i>

01:42:24.000 --> 01:42:29.082
<i>That might have been the result of the PTSD
he suffered after being tortured in Russia.</i>

01:42:29.083 --> 01:42:33.166
<i>But the question is not about Gumnaami Baba
or his followers' claims.</i>

01:42:33.167 --> 01:42:35.667
<i>The question is about his identity.</i>

01:42:36.042 --> 01:42:38.500
<i>Question is about the
proof of that identity.</i>

01:42:38.667 --> 01:42:40.625
Which I have submitted to the Commission.

01:42:41.750 --> 01:42:44.917
The answer, my friend,
is blowing in the wind.

01:42:45.375 --> 01:42:49.958
The problem is he wasn't an ordinary monk.

01:42:50.667 --> 01:42:56.167
He was an extraordinary soldier.
One of the greatest sons of India.

01:43:01.208 --> 01:43:03.542
Is that all, Mr. Dhar?

01:43:04.750 --> 01:43:07.291
- What?
- Or have you found anything else in your research?

01:43:07.292 --> 01:43:09.500
Yes, My Lord.

01:43:10.333 --> 01:43:12.000
I have, My Lord.

01:43:12.500 --> 01:43:16.292
The 2760 objects found
in Gumnaami Baba's room.

01:43:16.417 --> 01:43:19.082
Oh, what objects?

01:43:19.083 --> 01:43:23.792
First I'll tell you about
the hundreds of letters we found.

01:43:24.083 --> 01:43:29.667
<i>Pabitra Mohan Roy, Leela Roy, Sunil Das,
Anil Das, Ashutosh Kali, Bishwarup Roy...</i>

01:43:29.708 --> 01:43:31.999
<i>And many more freedom fighters
wrote to him...</i>

01:43:32.000 --> 01:43:38.750
And other well wishers who addressed him
as Netaji and asked him to be careful.

01:43:38.792 --> 01:43:43.625
In a letter to Netaji's dear friend
Dilip Roy, Leela Roy writes...

01:43:43.750 --> 01:43:46.292
that Netaji is alive and she has met him.

01:43:46.542 --> 01:43:50.292
But the most surprising thing is...

01:43:50.333 --> 01:43:53.250
<i>A letter signed by Secretary
Nathaniel Knowles...</i>

01:43:53.417 --> 01:43:57.500
An official letter from the
USA's Foreign Services...

01:43:57.792 --> 01:43:59.333
And where was that sent?

01:43:59.542 --> 01:44:04.333
It was sent to an ordinary monk
in Ayodhya.

01:44:04.750 --> 01:44:07.458
Interesting... Anything else?

01:44:07.500 --> 01:44:11.792
Yes, the details of the 2760 objects
have been submitted to the Commission.

01:44:11.958 --> 01:44:15.499
There were some really
interesting objects found.

01:44:15.500 --> 01:44:18.042
<i>Japanese water filters.</i>

01:44:18.417 --> 01:44:20.708
Flashlights from World War II.

01:44:21.250 --> 01:44:24.958
<i>German binoculars, pipes,
cigarettes, cigars.</i>

01:44:25.167 --> 01:44:26.792
<i>Bengali, English and Sanskrit...</i>

01:44:27.167 --> 01:44:28.541
Famous books in these languages.

01:44:28.542 --> 01:44:30.500
Numerous journals and magazines.

01:44:30.625 --> 01:44:33.042
Some rare photos of Netaji's parents
and family members.

01:44:33.208 --> 01:44:35.417
<i>Not just that.</i>

01:44:36.083 --> 01:44:40.042
There are notes on the back of the photos
in his own handwriting.

01:44:40.083 --> 01:44:48.083
We've found photos of many of his friends
with the mention of their nicknames.

01:44:48.875 --> 01:44:50.208
But the most important object...

01:44:50.250 --> 01:44:56.125
because of which a Government catalogue was
created and the objects kept with care...

01:44:56.208 --> 01:45:00.667
Lolita Bose, Netaji's niece
is the one who found it.

01:45:00.708 --> 01:45:03.875
I knew my uncle very well.

01:45:03.917 --> 01:45:07.667
He appreciated the finer things in life.

01:45:07.708 --> 01:45:12.375
Why would he live like a monk
in a place like this?

01:45:12.417 --> 01:45:14.250
All this is nonsense.

01:45:14.833 --> 01:45:16.917
This is rubbish!

01:45:44.750 --> 01:45:50.625
The first paper he found was the Khosla
Commission's original summons to Suresh Bose.

01:45:50.708 --> 01:45:51.333
Remember...

01:45:51.417 --> 01:45:52.792
<i>The original copy.</i>

01:45:53.375 --> 01:45:54.917
But it doesn't end there.

01:45:55.583 --> 01:45:59.958
She also found a copy of
Suresh Bose's dissentient report.

01:46:00.250 --> 01:46:03.916
That Suresh Bose had written
as a member of the Shahnawaz Committee.

01:46:03.917 --> 01:46:07.207
He had logically refuted the report.

01:46:07.208 --> 01:46:09.667
And he had said Subhas is alive.

01:46:10.292 --> 01:46:14.833
The second paper can be tracked down. But
the first one will be difficult to explain.

01:46:16.083 --> 01:46:17.375
No, My Lord.

01:46:18.625 --> 01:46:20.624
If the second document
would have been an ordinary copy...

01:46:20.625 --> 01:46:23.208
it would be easily accessed but...

01:46:24.208 --> 01:46:27.042
But it wasn't an ordinary copy.

01:46:27.250 --> 01:46:34.542
Because that had Lolita Bose's
mother's handwritten message.

01:46:36.792 --> 01:46:38.083
What was the message?

01:46:39.500 --> 01:46:42.750
"Dearest brother-in-law...

01:46:42.875 --> 01:46:45.208
May you have a long life.

01:46:45.833 --> 01:46:48.833
Lots of love and blessings."

01:46:49.208 --> 01:46:53.958
Addressed to her beloved brother-in-law.

01:46:54.667 --> 01:46:56.208
Subi!

01:46:57.375 --> 01:47:02.833
Subhas... Subhas Chandra Bose...

01:47:16.792 --> 01:47:18.458
Is that all?

01:47:22.875 --> 01:47:24.417
Yes, My Lord.

01:47:25.375 --> 01:47:26.750
Thank you.

01:47:26.958 --> 01:47:28.917
You may take your seat now.

01:47:35.250 --> 01:47:36.458
Thank you, My Lord.

01:47:36.583 --> 01:47:40.500
After six years of
extensive investigation...

01:47:40.708 --> 01:47:45.000
Finally, I've completed collecting
the entire evidence...

01:47:45.083 --> 01:47:47.207
all the testimonies...

01:47:47.208 --> 01:47:50.874
the report and findings
of the previous two commissions.

01:47:50.875 --> 01:47:55.749
I've been to Taiwan, Japan, Thailand,
London and Russia.

01:47:55.750 --> 01:47:59.250
And conducted in-depth queries
with all the witnesses.

01:48:00.208 --> 01:48:05.083
I will duly table the report at
the Parliament in a few months.

01:48:06.375 --> 01:48:10.958
This Commission now
officially comes to an end.

01:48:24.375 --> 01:48:25.542
What is the stress?

01:48:26.000 --> 01:48:27.375
Confirmed, tomorrow?

01:48:27.917 --> 01:48:29.458
Yeah, that's what I heard.

01:48:30.583 --> 01:48:32.458
Does Sumit have any information?

01:48:32.625 --> 01:48:34.042
No.

01:48:34.250 --> 01:48:35.958
But most probably, it's tomorrow.

01:48:36.500 --> 01:48:38.375
Expect the worst, Chandrachur.

01:48:38.667 --> 01:48:41.417
You know how it went
with Shahnawaz and Khosla.

01:48:41.958 --> 01:48:43.624
Adheer is right.

01:48:43.625 --> 01:48:45.583
People will shout and scream.

01:48:45.708 --> 01:48:47.917
It'll fizzle out in Delhi.

01:48:48.250 --> 01:48:51.375
But they're under a lot of pressure...

01:48:52.458 --> 01:48:55.917
Anuj, get the door please.

01:48:56.875 --> 01:49:00.250
I raised some fundamental points.

01:49:02.083 --> 01:49:04.625
- But now if they... What?
- Hey!

01:49:05.208 --> 01:49:07.333
Your wife...

01:49:10.375 --> 01:49:12.292
Am I disturbing you?

01:49:12.333 --> 01:49:13.708
No, not at all.

01:49:13.833 --> 01:49:15.042
Come in.

01:49:15.083 --> 01:49:20.792
I thought it is a big day for all of you,
so will come and wish you all the best.

01:49:20.833 --> 01:49:23.250
Thank you. Thank you.
How did you know?

01:49:23.625 --> 01:49:25.813
Newspaper, TV... It's everywhere.

01:49:26.500 --> 01:49:27.542
Well...

01:49:28.333 --> 01:49:29.625
- We'll get going now.
- What?

01:49:29.667 --> 01:49:31.374
No, I'll push off.
You guys stay please...

01:49:31.375 --> 01:49:35.792
- No, no...
- Please stay.

01:49:35.917 --> 01:49:38.542
- See you tomorrow in the morning.
- We'll leave.

01:49:38.583 --> 01:49:39.707
- Okay...
- Let's go.

01:49:39.708 --> 01:49:42.332
- Okay, good night.
- Bye.

01:49:42.333 --> 01:49:45.583
- What are you staring at?
- Hey, pass me my bag.

01:49:45.750 --> 01:49:48.582
- Anuj, call me in the morning.
- Okay.

01:49:48.583 --> 01:49:50.833
Adheer, take the print outs.

01:49:51.875 --> 01:49:53.083
But that's my shoe.

01:50:09.083 --> 01:50:11.167
Can I get you a drink?

01:50:11.500 --> 01:50:12.542
Okay.

01:50:12.667 --> 01:50:13.667
What do you want?

01:50:14.000 --> 01:50:17.167
- The usual. Rum and Coke.
- Okay.

01:50:20.875 --> 01:50:25.250
You know, of the people
who knew Gumnaami Baba...

01:50:25.500 --> 01:50:27.999
one of them was Colonel VR Mohan.

01:50:28.000 --> 01:50:30.582
The owner of the famous
Mohan Meakin Breweries.

01:50:30.583 --> 01:50:34.333
He wrote some letters to Baba
in the '50s.

01:50:34.792 --> 01:50:40.083
Later on, he named the best selling product
of his company after Gumnaami Baba.

01:50:40.583 --> 01:50:42.000
Which one?

01:50:43.917 --> 01:50:45.042
This...

01:50:45.958 --> 01:50:47.333
Old Monk.

01:50:48.208 --> 01:50:50.500
Great trivia!

01:50:50.542 --> 01:50:52.833
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

01:50:55.458 --> 01:50:58.667
- It's too stiff.
- Here's some water.

01:51:06.583 --> 01:51:08.250
Are you okay?

01:51:08.958 --> 01:51:10.625
Are you okay?

01:51:12.458 --> 01:51:19.125
All of life's struggles and fights
culminates to just one night.

01:51:21.792 --> 01:51:23.083
I see.

01:51:24.917 --> 01:51:26.375
Are you very tense?

01:51:27.083 --> 01:51:30.042
Not like the board exams but yes.

01:51:35.125 --> 01:51:38.375
So, the thing is...

01:51:40.292 --> 01:51:45.083
Can I stay over tonight?

01:51:46.292 --> 01:51:47.292
What?

01:51:52.917 --> 01:51:56.792
How does a marriage become better
after divorce?

01:52:58.917 --> 01:53:00.750
Chandrachur.

01:53:05.083 --> 01:53:06.292
Who are you?

01:53:06.917 --> 01:53:11.375
Can't you recognise the person
you've been researching?

01:53:13.292 --> 01:53:14.583
Oh!

01:53:15.042 --> 01:53:18.292
- You are...
- Yes, you're right...

01:53:19.792 --> 01:53:22.375
What's happening?
You're dead.

01:53:24.333 --> 01:53:26.458
I am dead.

01:53:27.083 --> 01:53:32.542
But not because my heart stopped beating
or my body was cremated.

01:53:37.833 --> 01:53:38.833
Then?

01:53:40.792 --> 01:53:44.750
A soldier doesn't die
when he becomes a martyr.

01:53:44.792 --> 01:53:48.083
He dies when people forget him.

01:53:48.292 --> 01:53:56.124
A monk dies when people call out his name
for the last time.

01:53:56.125 --> 01:53:58.499
Then there's no death for you, sir.

01:53:58.500 --> 01:54:03.541
People still remember you...
Especially as Netaji, very well.

01:54:03.542 --> 01:54:09.500
Oh, Netaji is at the airport
and at a busy intersection on horseback!

01:54:09.792 --> 01:54:11.750
You call that remembering?

01:54:14.833 --> 01:54:16.124
No, sir.

01:54:16.125 --> 01:54:21.916
As long as I'm here, we are here,
Mission Netaji is here...

01:54:21.917 --> 01:54:22.958
I know.

01:54:23.625 --> 01:54:26.083
That's why, I have some advice
about tomorrow.

01:54:27.750 --> 01:54:30.166
Don't worry about the result.

01:54:30.167 --> 01:54:37.792
No matter what the results are tomorrow,
keep up your work.

01:54:39.417 --> 01:54:41.333
What's going to happen tomorrow?

01:54:43.875 --> 01:54:45.208
I don't know.

01:54:47.708 --> 01:54:49.458
Only Time knows.

01:54:49.667 --> 01:54:52.417
But you yourself are Time!

01:54:53.500 --> 01:55:01.500
You used to sign your name as Mahakaal
meaning Time in your letters.

01:55:08.917 --> 01:55:11.458
Bhagwanji!

01:55:15.375 --> 01:55:17.042
Bhagwanji!

01:55:19.833 --> 01:55:21.792
Come, come.

01:55:21.833 --> 01:55:23.000
Has anything come out?

01:55:23.042 --> 01:55:26.208
- Plane crash theory has been rejected.
- Good!

01:55:26.292 --> 01:55:28.833
- What else?
- Yes, telling you.

01:55:29.333 --> 01:55:31.082
- Morning.
- Good morning.

01:55:31.083 --> 01:55:33.167
- Good morning!
- Good morning!

01:55:33.500 --> 01:55:34.583
Morning!

01:55:34.833 --> 01:55:36.500
Okay, listen to this.

01:55:37.625 --> 01:55:42.332
"On a conspectus of all the facts and
circumstances relevant to the above issues...

01:55:42.333 --> 01:55:47.750
it stands established
that emplaning at Saigon on 17.8.1945...

01:55:47.792 --> 01:55:51.124
Netaji succeeded in evading
the Allied forces...

01:55:51.125 --> 01:55:53.166
and escaping out of their reach.

01:55:53.167 --> 01:55:58.082
And as a camouflage thereof the entire
make believe story of the air crash...

01:55:58.083 --> 01:56:03.749
Netaji's death therein and his cremation was
engineered by the Japanese army authorities...

01:56:03.750 --> 01:56:07.291
including the two doctors
and Habibur Rehman.

01:56:07.292 --> 01:56:13.167
And then aired on 23.8.1945
through a statement prepared by SA Ayer...

01:56:13.250 --> 01:56:15.874
at the dictation of the aforementioned
authorities...

01:56:15.875 --> 01:56:20.041
to give imprimatur of INA
to the death news of Netaji."

01:56:20.042 --> 01:56:22.083
Yes! Yes!

01:56:22.167 --> 01:56:23.582
What about the ashes
in the Renkoji Temple?

01:56:23.583 --> 01:56:24.874
Yeah...

01:56:24.875 --> 01:56:27.917
"Since ashes collected
were Ichiro Okura's...

01:56:27.958 --> 01:56:29.207
not of Netaji...

01:56:29.208 --> 01:56:33.125
the only inference drawn is that the ashes
lying in the temple is not that of Netaji."

01:56:35.000 --> 01:56:36.082
What have they said about Russia?

01:56:36.083 --> 01:56:37.792
Russia... yeah.

01:56:37.833 --> 01:56:43.583
"But the question whether Netaji
thereafter landed in Russia or elsewhere...

01:56:43.667 --> 01:56:47.583
cannot be answered due
to dearth of evidence."

01:56:48.250 --> 01:56:52.249
Even I thought this might happen.
Anyway, let it be.

01:56:52.250 --> 01:56:54.625
And Gumnaami Baba?

01:56:55.583 --> 01:56:57.042
You read it out.

01:56:57.333 --> 01:57:00.708
- Someone read it out.
- Read...

01:57:07.750 --> 01:57:11.124
"Apparently, there's no reason for not
acting or relying upon the evidence...

01:57:11.125 --> 01:57:12.957
of the last two categories
of witnesses.

01:57:12.958 --> 01:57:16.917
Particularly of the category
who had seen Netaji before 1945...

01:57:17.167 --> 01:57:22.624
and also met Bhagwanji/Gumnaami Baba
face to face on a number of occasions.

01:57:22.625 --> 01:57:26.457
More so in their evidence regarding the
frequent visit of some freedom fighters...

01:57:26.458 --> 01:57:31.749
eminent politicians and former members of INA on
January 23rd and during the Durga festival..."

01:57:31.750 --> 01:57:34.167
- So? So? So? Then what?
- But as...

01:57:34.875 --> 01:57:36.500
Why apparently?

01:57:37.000 --> 01:57:40.874
"But as the discussion will follow there are
other formidable facts and circumstances..."

01:57:40.875 --> 01:57:45.042
What facts and circumstances?
Tell me in short.

01:57:53.125 --> 01:57:55.749
"In fine, the absence
of any clinching evidence...

01:57:55.750 --> 01:57:58.624
to prove that
Bhagwanji/Gumnaami Baba was Netaji.

01:57:58.625 --> 01:58:04.792
The question whether he died in Faizabad
on 16.9.1985 need not be answered."

01:58:07.125 --> 01:58:09.417
They don't need to answer questions
about Netaji?

01:58:10.667 --> 01:58:12.417
Is this a joke?

01:58:12.458 --> 01:58:15.582
Are we talking about the grocer
or the local laundry guy?

01:58:15.583 --> 01:58:18.957
They said they can't come to any conclusions
after the handwriting analysis.

01:58:18.958 --> 01:58:19.958
What?

